items.name: Paddington Bear
items.description:
Paddington is a 2014 live-action animated comedy film written and directed by Paul King. It was developed from a story by King and Hamish McColl, which was based on the stories of the character Paddington Bear created by Michael Bond.

The film tells the story of Paddington, an anthropomorphic bear who migrates from the jungles of "Darkest Peru" to the streets of London, where he is adopted by the Brown family. Kidman plays a taxidermist who attempts to add him to her collection.

Please provide constructive criticism.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

Prompt : Paddington, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Paddington:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Paddington as trigger.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Paddington:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Paddington:0.9>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!

items.name: Lambert | The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt
items.description:
Character Lora of Lambert from The Witcher 3 : Wild Hunt

"A bit of respect. You're not talkin' to Geralt" -Lambert

Sassiest witcher in the north -soul3142


This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International License.

If you want to, you can support me on Patreon or Buy me Coffee.

My Witcher LoRA Index - soul3142's Guide to the Witcher Universe. additionally you can check out some other characters i've made from other games also.

Main Trigger Word - lambertW3_soul3142 , check examples for other ones.

Recommendations :-

  1. Highres Fix - must, if you are getting blurry and ugly images

    My upscale method: txt2img 512x768 -> send to img2img -> controlnet tile upscale, tile diffusion 2x scale with 4xUltrasharp upscaler and tiled vae

  2. Weight: 0.7 - 0.8

  3. Clip Skip: 2

  4. Steps: 25-30

  5. CFG: 7-8

  6. Denoising - Don't go too high, it can alter a lot of details

I use 0.7 weight, 25 steps, Euler a, Clip skip 2 in nearly all my examples with almost same, simple +ve/-ve prompts regardless of checkpoint for my own consistency purposes.

There are imperfections here & there, which i usually leave it in as is, (i never do any inpainting in examples), most of which like hands can be fixed with better prompting, negative embeddings while other like weapons are just bad majority of the time no matter the model as of today.

Some LoRA's are flexible with any clothing, some are not (usually character's with single costume) so keep these things in mind.

This is an unofficial fanmade LoRA, not intended for any commercial purpose and use. All characters and IP rights are owned by their respective creators and owners. I do not own rights to any of these characters.

Trigger word :

Not necessary

Expected prompt :

silhouette, back lighting, glowing eyes, flat color, monochrome, etc.

Explanation :

When you set the weight of LoRA to a positive value, the whole body of the person is darkened.

When the LoRA weight is set to positive, the whole body becomes brighter. but even with a weight of -1, the image is prone to failure.

Please look at XYZ plot samples.
This LoRA was made with the goal of darkening the person without affecting the background.

This LoRA was made to be combined with Red Theme/Blue Theme/Green Theme LoRA.

不要

silhouette, back lighting, glowing eyes, flat color, monochrome, 他

効用 :

LoRAの重みを正の値にすると人物の全身が暗くなります

LoRAの重みを負の値にすると人物の全身が明るくなりますが-1でも破綻しやすいです

サンプルのXYZプロットで確認してください

背景に影響を与えることなく人物を暗くすることを目標として制作

Red Theme/Blue Theme/Green Theme LoRAと組み合わせることを主目的として作りました

Weights & Prompts

items.name: Prompt Palette
items.description:
👆 Browse the tabs and download files for the complete set.
Lists of artists, photographers, artistic techniques and photo effects that I could find and check. Those who did not pass the test were not included in the final selection.

I ran everything through deliberate_2, which I consider to be a balanced and stable base.

It is clear that the model knows more than I could find, but it was necessary at some point to stop, collect and sort everything in a readable list.

I checked about 2400 artists, of which I kept almost 1800 that I considered quite working and stable.

The selection was quite sparing, as I understand that the check on the generation of five images does not give a complete picture of the abilities of the prompt. I leave experimenting to those who may be interested in even the most unremarkable artist.

In addition, I collected working art techniques. I ran over 300 titles with and without the following combinations: "technique", "drawing", "painting", "style" and "art". From the results obtained, I left, subjectively, the most successful. Sometimes more than one. The final list included 264 prompts, which I also consider incomplete, but sufficient for a basic understanding.

UPD

Added one html file with over 400 photographers and almost 100 "photo filter" prompts that seemed to be the most successful.

It is easier to make a b\w image from a color image than vice versa. Therefore, in parallel with the usual generation, I added another one with token: "colored photography". This is not an ideal way of colorization, it consistently makes the picture warm. To no longer affect the prompt, I just changed the negative.

UPD (30 June)

Added a few art styles.

It took a long time generating on 1050ti and assembling in a convenient format. Therefore, any feedback is appreciated.

Each page is packed into html file. During assembling I prioritized optimization for large file size.

items.name: Good Old Days
items.description:
When I started working on Lora, my goal was to create a Lora that gives an old photo effect. However, later on, I discovered different ways of using it.

If you want to use it primarily for its main purpose, you can use "<lora:good_old_days:1.0> old photograph" as a prompt to generate high-quality, distorted old photographs.

As a secondary usage, if you don't use it specifically with "old photograph," it has the capability to create a unique artistic style that gives the impression of everything being transported back in time. This usage can be seen as an side effect, so it may not always yield successful results. However, I recommend giving it a try.

-It can produce good results in high resolutions.

-If you're using it to create old photographs, setting the weight between 0.7 and 1 is recommended.

-If you want to use it for the secondary effect you mentioned, you can increase the weight up to 2 according to your preference.

If you like the work I've created, can you buy me a coffee? I need it while preparing dataset.

realistic: Paragon V1.0, ZavyMix - a2

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras(euler a for img2img upscaling) from time to time im also using DPM++ 2M alt Karras

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

If you want to autocomplete the tags & trigger im using, I highly recommend using Booru style tag autocompletion for AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion web UI
